[{"location":"gallery/brightness_pixel_location/#Finding-the-brightest-pixel","page":"Finding the brightest pixel","title":"Finding the brightest pixel","text":"Reference: corresponding sunpy webpage.\n\nusing SunPy, PythonCall\nusing SunPy: Map\n@py import sunpy.data.sample: AIA_171_IMAGE\n@py import astropy.units as u\n\naia = Map(AIA_171_IMAGE)\npixel_pos = Tuple(argmax(aia')) .* u.pixel\nhpc_max = aia.wcs.pixel_to_world(pixel_pos...)\n\nLetâ€™s now plot the results.\n\n@py import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nfig = plt.figure()\nax = fig.add_subplot(projection=aia)\naia.plot(axes=ax)\nax.plot_coord(hpc_max, \"wx\", fillstyle=\"none\", markersize=10)\nfig","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/brightness_pixel_location/#Acceleration","page":"Finding the brightest pixel","title":"Acceleration","text":"using Chairmarks\n@py import numpy as np\n\n@b sunpy.map.Map(AIA_171_IMAGE) @py(np.argwhere(_.data == _.data.max()))\n@b Map(AIA_171_IMAGE) argmax(_')","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorials/coordinates/#Coordinates","page":"Coordinates","title":"Coordinates","text":"This section of the guide introduces how coordinates are represented in sunpy.\n\nReference: corresponding sunpy webpage.\n\nusing SunPy\nusing SunPy: SkyCoord\nusing PythonCall\n@py import astropy.units as u\n@py import sunpy.coordinates.frames as frames\n\ncoord = SkyCoord(70*u.deg, -30*u.deg, obstime=\"2017-08-01\",\n                 frame=frames.HeliographicStonyhurst)\n\ncoord.transform_to(frames.Helioprojective(observer=\"earth\"))\n\n@py import sunpy.data.sample: AIA_171_IMAGE \n@py import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\namap = sunpy.map.Map(AIA_171_IMAGE)\ncoord = SkyCoord(100 * u.arcsec, 10*u.arcsec, frame=amap.coordinate_frame)\npixels = amap.wcs.world_to_pixel(coord)\n\nfig = plt.figure()\nax = plt.subplot(projection=amap)\namap.plot()\nax.plot_coord(coord, 'o')\nfig","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/map_contouring/#Finding-contours-of-a-map","page":"Finding contours of a map","title":"Finding contours of a map","text":"This example shows how to find and plot contours on a map.\n\nReference: corresponding sunpy webpage\n\nusing SunPy, PythonCall\nusing SunPy: Map\n@py import sunpy.data.sample: AIA_193_IMAGE\n@py import astropy.units as u\n\naiamap = Map(AIA_193_IMAGE)\n\ncontours =  SunPy.find_contours_py(aiamap, 50000.0)\ncontours_py =  aiamap.find_contours(50000 * u.DN)\n\n@py import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nlet fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n    # First subplot: Julia implementation\n    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1, projection=aiamap)\n    # aiamap.plot(axes=ax)\n    ax.plot_coord.(contours)\n    ax.set_title(\"Julia find_contours\")\n\n    # Second subplot: Python implementation\n    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection=aiamap)\n    # aiamap.plot(axes=ax2)\n    ax2.plot_coord.(PyList(contours_py))\n    ax2.set_title(\"Python find_contours\")\n\n    fig\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/map_contouring/#Acceleration","page":"Finding contours of a map","title":"Acceleration","text":"using Chairmarks\n\n# Python\n@b aiamap.find_contours(50000 * u.DN)\n\n# vs Julia\n@b SunPy.find_contours_py(aiamap, 50000.0)","category":"section"},{"location":"#SunPy","page":"Home","title":"SunPy","text":"A Julia wrapper around SunPy.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Motivation","page":"Home","title":"Motivation","text":"This package brings SunPy's solar physics capabilities to Julia, enabling:\n\nPerformant Array manipulation: Leverage Julia's powerful and flexible array manipulation for accelerated numerical computations\nEcosystem integration: Combine solar data analysis with the broader Julia scientific computing stack (e.g., SciML, JuliaAstro, JuliaArrays)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Acquiring-Data","page":"Home","title":"Acquiring Data","text":"Obtaining solar data using the Fido interface (a unified data search and retrieval tool). \n\nusing SunPy, PythonCall\n@py import sunpy.net: Fido, attrs as a\nFido\nFido.search(a.Time(\"2012/3/4\", \"2012/3/6\"), a.Instrument.lyra, a.Level.two)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Maps","page":"Home","title":"Maps","text":"Map object in sunpy.\n\n@py import sunpy.data.sample: AIA_171_IMAGE\nmy_map = sunpy.map.Map(AIA_171_IMAGE)","category":"section"},{"location":"#API","page":"Home","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#SunPy.find_contours_py-Tuple{SunPy.Map, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SunPy.find_contours_py","text":"find_contours_py(m::Map, levels)\n\nFind contours in a Map at specified levels and convert them to world coordinates (SkyCoord) using the map's WCS transformation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
